---
alwaysApply: true
---
This repository uses modern C++23.

General guidelines:

- Prefer RAII.
- Use std::unique_ptr for ownership.
- Do not use raw owning pointers (Qt parented-new for widgets is allowed).
- Prefer std::jthread over std::thread.
- Avoid global state.
- Keep headers lightweight.
- Separate interface and implementation.
- Minimize lock contention.
- Every class should have a single responsibility (App is the allowed composition root).
- Workers never make scheduling decisions.
- Scheduler owns every Action.
- Preserve strict FIFO ordering within channels.
- Do not implement future phases until requested.
